{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require cosmetic surgeons to hold a GMC-approved specialist qualification",
        "additional_details": "This legislation should acknowledge cosmetic surgery as a specialist branch of surgery and be a legally protected title, by creating a specialist pathway for cosmetic surgery with training /FRCS qualification status, and a transparent route to transfer skills from other branches of medical training. This could keep public safe & prevent cosmetic cowboy clinics from recruiting potentially lower grade doctors and prevent doctors with no surgical speciality from causing catastrophic injury to patients.",
        "background": "Require clinicians carrying out cosmetic procedures to hold a GMC-approved specialist qualification for surgical intervention for the area of the anatomy that they are treating.  A new law should ensure that any clinician carrying out surgery should have a GMC-recognised specialist qualification.",
